From: Kahan, T.L. & LaBerge, S. (1994).
Lucid dreaming as metacognition: implications for cognitive science.
Consciousness and Cognition, 3 (2), pp.246--264.


p.249:
Part of a written dream report:

I'm in a crowded library walking towards a large desk. The heels of my shoes
make a clicking sound on the stone floor that echoes through the room. (* I'M
THINKING TO MYSELF `I hope this noise doesn't distract the people around me.'*)
